5-67:Figure 6 illustrates our results when the set r of expansion terms is used .
5-68:They show that matching the ads to the terms in the set r instead of to the triggering page p (AAK T strategy) leads to a considerable improvement over our baseline, AAK .
5-69:The gain is even larger when we use the terms in r to expand the triggering page (AAK EXP method) .
5-70:This confirms our hypothesis that the triggering page could have some interesting terms that should not be completely discarded .
5-71:Finally, we analyze the impact on the ranking of using the contents of pages pointed by the ads .
5-72:Figure 7 displays our results .
5-73:It is clear that using only the contents of the pages pointed by the ads (H strategy) yields very poor results .
5-74:However, combining evidence from the pages pointed by the ads with our baseline yields improved results .
5-75:Most important, combining our best strategy so far (AAK EXP) with pages pointed by ads (AAK EXP H strategy) leads to superior results .
5-76:This happens because the two additional sources of evidence, expansion terms and pages pointed by the ads, are distinct and complementary, providing extra and valuable information for matching ads to a Web page .
